>> source: https://www.eatingwell.com/recipe/8032579/best-egg-salad-recipe/
>> total time: 15 minutes
>> serves: 4

Stir @celery{2%hearts}, @onion or shallot{1/4%cup} and @champagne vinegar{1%Tbsp} together in a #medium bowl{}; let stand at room temperature until the onion is bright red, about ~{5%minutes}.

Add @hard-boiled egg{8} halves to the bowl; mash with a fork until finely crumbled. Add @Greek yogurt{2%Tbsp}, @yellow mustard{1%Tbsp}, @mayonnaise{1%Tbsp}, @dill{1%tsp}, @chives{1%tsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and @pepper{1/4%tsp}; stir until well combined. Garnish with additional dill and chives, if desired.
